# Implementation Plan - CRM Backend & Integration

This plan outlines the design and implementation of a production-ready Node.js/Express.js backend written in TypeScript, integrated with a PostgreSQL database via Prisma ORM, using JWT authentication, and connected to the Next.js frontend.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **PostgreSQL Instance**: We assume a local or cloud PostgreSQL instance is available. We will output the `.env` configuration file with placeholder credentials, which you can customize.
> - **Authentication Flow**: Since the current frontend has no login/signup screens (it automatically starts with `Sarah Chen` as admin), we will build a sleek and modern **Login/Signup Page** on the frontend that redirects unauthenticated users and stores the JWT securely in `localStorage`.
> - **Workspace Configuration**: We will default configure CORS to allow requests from `http://localhost:3000` (Next.js default) and run the Express API on port `5000`.

## Architecture & Scalable Folder Structure

The backend will follow a clean, modular architecture:

- **Routes**: Define endpoints and apply validation and authentication middleware.
- **Controllers**: Handle HTTP requests/responses, extract parameters, and call service layers.
- **Services**: Contain all core business logic and direct database queries using Prisma.
- **Middleware**: Custom error handling, JWT parsing, and input schema validations (using `zod`).
- **Validations**: Define request body validation schemas using `zod`.
- **Config**: Set up variables, database client instances, and utility setups.
- **Utils**: Custom error classes, response helpers, and cryptographic utils.

